Simulation for the selection of bivariate parametric families

Source: R/XVineFamSelSimul.R
XVineFamSelSimul.Rd

XVineFamSelSimul returns simulation results of selecting bivariate parametric families by calling the function XVineFamSel(). All information about the simulation result is saved in the list of FamSelOut.

Usage

XVineFamSelSimul(
  N,
  Rank = TRUE,
  qt,
  ite,
  XVS,
  edgeIndex,
  familyset_tc,
  familyset_cop,
  selectioncrit = "AIC",
  effsampsize = 10,
  tau_threshold = 0.05
)

Arguments

N

Numeric; the sample size.

Rank

Logical; whether rank transformation is performed or not (Rank=T; default).

qt

Numeric; a lower enough threshold used in the rank transformation (e.g. switches from Pareto scale to uniform scale)

ite

Numeric; the number of iterations for simulation.

XVS

A list consisting of three components: reconstructed structure matrices, family matrices, parameter matrices, see:XVineSpec().

edgeIndex

Numeric vector; the index set that indicates the location of the matrix for the corresponding edge.

familyset_tc

Numeric vector; the model type of bivariate tail copulas. Possible tail copula models are:

  • 1=Husler-Reiss model

  • 2=Negative logistic model

  • 3=Logistic model

  • 4=Dirichlet model

familyset_cop

Numeric vector; the class of bivariate copula families with a single parameter.

selectioncrit

Character; the information criteria for model selections (default: AIC).

effsampsize

Integer; indicates the effective sample size (Default: 10) for the independence copula.

tau_threshold

Numeric; indicates the value of the Kendall's tau (Default: 0.05) for the independence copula.

Value

  1. FamSelOut: A list of \(d\times d\) strict upper triangular matrices from the function XVineFamSel() for iterations.

  2. EffSizePercent: A \(d\times d\) strict upper triangular matrix including the percentages of the effective sample size.

  3. GlobalProp: Numeric; the proportion of correctly selected families over all trees.

  4. TreeProp: Numeric vector; the proportion of correctly selected families for each level tree.

  5. EdgeProp: A \(d\times d\) strict upper triangular matrix including the proportion of correctly selected families for each edge in each tree.

  6. SelectIndCop: Numeric; the number of times the algorithm chooses the independence copula for the specified edge by edgeIndex.
